HEADWORD: Procrustes
<hw>Pro*crus"tes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/,
fr. <?/ to beat out, to stretch; <?/ forward + <?/ to strike.]</ety>
<fld>(Gr. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A celebrated legendary highwayman of
Attica, who tied his victims upon an iron bed, and, as the case
required, either stretched or cut of their legs to adapt them to its
length; -- whence the metaphorical phrase, <col><b><it>the bed of
Procrustes</it></b></col>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Procrustesian</ent>⟦br⟧
